        <h1>Baseball Slugging Percentage</h1>
       =20
          <p class=3D"lead">Slugging percentage (SLG) is a measure of the b=
atting productivity of a hitter,defined as the total bases divided by the n=
umber of at bats.</p>
       =20
       =20
       =20
       =20
          <div class=3D"details">
            <p>Slugging percentage is the sum of bases made by the batter (=
singles, doubles, triples and home runs) divided by number of at bats.</p>
          </div>
       =20
       =20
       =20
       =20
